## Security Review

### High Issue: Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) Vulnerability

**Location:** Line 2

**Problem:** Using `innerHTML` with user input allows attackers to inject malicious scripts.

```javascript
// VULNERABLE
element.innerHTML = userInput;

// SECURE - Use textContent
element.textContent = userInput;

// Or sanitize if HTML needed
element.innerHTML = DOMPurify.sanitize(userInput);
```

**Recommendation:** Always escape untrusted user input or use a sanitization library.
